						<summary>

						<p>On the stone pedestal of the Nandi in the <hi rend="italic">garbhagṛiha</hi> in the Īśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Sadāśiva, 1558 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka [1]479, Piṅgaḷa, ba. 30, Śivarātri</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1558 A.D., February 18, (Friday).</hi></p>						

						<p>The inscription is damaged and registers a grant of land to god Sōmēśvara of Siripi by Kṛishṇappa-Nāyaka Koṇḍappa-Nāyaka.</p>						

						</summary>
